(basic program for c)
#include<stdio.h>

int main() {
    printf("hello world!!");
    return 0;
}


variables:
It is the name of a memory location which stores some data.

basic program of variable
#include <stdio.h>
int main(){
    int number =45;
    char star='*';
    int age =22;
    float pi=3.14;
    return 0;
}

where number,star,age,pi are variable in which we store value.

rules to write variables in c language:
a. Variables are case sensitive

b. 1st character is alphabet or '_'

c. no comma/blank space

d. No other symbol other than '_'

value of variable can be changed. name of variable should be meaning full.

singel quots('') are used in c language.

